---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Temple Protocols & Purity Guidelines | Sree Vishwanagayakshi Temple">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="proto-hero">
    <div class="proto-hero-content">
      <div class="proto-eyebrow">Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple</div>
      <h1>Temple Protocols</h1>
      <p>Sacred purity guidelines to be observed before visiting the temple</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <section class="proto-intro">
    <div class="proto-container">
      <p class="intro-text">
        The divine presence at Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple is maintained through strict adherence
        to traditional purity observances. These are not mere customs &#8212; they are sacred protocols
        established by our ancestors to preserve the spiritual potency of the rituals and ensure that
        devotees receive the full blessings of the Naga deities. Please read and follow these guidelines
        before planning your visit or participating in any pooja.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Protocols -->
  <section class="proto-section">
    <div class="proto-container">

      <div class="proto-card">
        <div class="proto-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M18 8h1a4 4 0 0 1 0 8h-1"/>
            <path d="M2 8h16v9a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H6a4 4 0 0 1-4-4V8z"/>
            <line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="4"/>
            <line x1="10" y1="1" x2="10" y2="4"/>
            <line x1="14" y1="1" x2="14" y2="4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="proto-content">
          <h2>Alcohol &amp; Intoxicants</h2>
          <p class="proto-rule">Do not consume alcohol or any intoxicating substance before visiting the temple.</p>
          <p class="proto-detail">
            Entering the sacred premises under the influence of alcohol or intoxicants is strictly prohibited.
            Such substances disturb the mind and body, making one spiritually impure and unfit for divine
            darshan. Please ensure you are completely sober before entering the temple compound.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="proto-card">
        <div class="proto-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <circle cx="12" cy="12" r="10"/>
            <polyline points="12 6 12 12 16 14"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="proto-content">
          <h2>Menstrual Cycle</h2>
          <p class="proto-rule">During the menstrual period and for 7 days thereafter, ladies should not visit the temple. From the 8th day, one may come.</p>
          <p class="proto-detail">
            This observance is rooted in the traditional understanding of the body&#8217;s energy cycles.
            The first 7 days of the cycle are considered a period of rest and internal purification.
            From the 8th day onward, a lady is considered ritually pure and is welcome to visit the
            temple and participate in all poojas.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="proto-card">
        <div class="proto-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-4-4H5a4 4 0 0 0-4 4v2"/>
            <circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/>
            <path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 0 0-3-3.87"/>
            <path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 0 1 0 7.75"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="proto-content">
          <h2>Death in the Family</h2>
          <p class="proto-rule">After a death in the family, do not visit the temple for 14 days.</p>
          <p class="proto-detail">
            When a death occurs in the immediate family, the household observes a mourning period
            of 14 days. During this time, family members are in a state of ritual impurity (ashaucha)
            and should refrain from temple visits and participation in poojas. After the 14-day period
            and the completion of prescribed mourning rites, one may return to the temple.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="proto-card">
        <div class="proto-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5">
            <path d="M3 11l19-9-9 19-2-8-8-2z"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <div class="proto-content">
          <h2>Non-Vegetarian Food</h2>
          <p class="proto-rule">Do not visit the temple on the same day you have consumed non-vegetarian food.</p>
          <p class="proto-detail">
            The consumption of meat, fish, or eggs creates a state of ritual impurity that is
            incompatible with entering the sacred space of the Naga deities. On days you plan to
            visit the temple or participate in a pooja, please observe a purely vegetarian diet.
            This applies to the day of the visit.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Notice -->
  <section class="proto-notice">
    <div class="proto-container">
      <div class="notice-box">
        <h3>A Note from Ambotti Thampuran</h3>
        <blockquote>
          &#8220;These protocols are not meant to exclude anyone. They exist to protect the devotee&#8217;s
          own spiritual experience and to preserve the sanctity of this sacred space. When we approach
          the divine in a state of purity, the blessings flow freely and completely. We welcome every
          devotee with open arms &#8212; at the right time and in the right state of readiness.&#8221;
        </blockquote>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="proto-cta">
    <div class="proto-container">
      <h2>Ready to Visit?</h2>
      <p>Plan your visit to Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple</p>
      <div class="cta-buttons">
        <a href="/visit" class="btn btn-primary">Plan Your Visit</a>
        <a href="/poojas" class="btn btn-primary">Book a Pooja</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
.proto-hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 55vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background:
    linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(45, 24, 16, 0.65), rgba(122, 25, 18, 0.92)),
    url('/images/temple%20main%20entrance.jpg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
  text-align: center;
  border-bottom: 8px solid var(--saffron);
}

.proto-hero-content {
  max-width: 800px;
}

.proto-eyebrow {
  font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--gold-light);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 5px;
  margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.proto-hero h1 {
  font-size: 4.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--bg-base);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  text-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0,0,0,0.6);
}

.proto-hero p {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  color: var(--bg-alt);
  font-style: italic;
  opacity: 0.9;
}

/* Intro */
.proto-intro {
  padding: 4rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
}

.proto-container {
  max-width: 960px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

.intro-text {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  text-align: center;
}

/* Protocol Cards */
.proto-section {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.proto-card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 80px 1fr;
  gap: 2.5rem;
  align-items: start;
  padding: 3rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  border-left: 6px solid var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(122, 25, 18, 0.07);
}

.proto-card:last-child {
  margin-bottom: 0;
}

.proto-icon svg {
  width: 52px;
  height: 52px;
  color: var(--saffron);
  margin-top: 0.4rem;
}

.proto-content h2 {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 2rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
}

.proto-rule {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  padding: 1rem 1.2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--saffron);
  font-style: italic;
}

.proto-detail {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.85;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

/* Notice */
.proto-notice {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--laterite-dark);
}

.notice-box {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  text-align: center;
}

.notice-box h3 {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 1.6rem;
  color: var(--gold-light);
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 2px;
}

.notice-box blockquote {
  font-family: 'Source Serif 4', serif;
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--bg-alt);
  font-style: italic;
  border-left: 4px solid var(--saffron);
  padding-left: 2rem;
  text-align: left;
}

/* CTA */
.proto-cta {
  padding: 5rem 2rem;
  background: var(--laterite-red);
  text-align: center;
  border-top: 8px solid var(--saffron);
}

.proto-cta h2 {
  font-family: 'Playfair Display', serif;
  font-size: 3rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--bg-base);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.proto-cta p {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  color: var(--gold-light);
  margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  font-style: italic;
}

.cta-buttons {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  justify-content: center;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}

.cta-buttons .btn-primary {
  background: var(--bg-base) !important;
  color: var(--laterite-red) !important;
  border-color: var(--bg-base) !important;
  box-shadow: 0 6px 0 rgba(45, 24, 16, 0.4) !important;
}

.cta-buttons .btn-primary:hover {
  background: var(--gold-light) !important;
  color: var(--laterite-dark) !important;
}

/* Responsive */
@media (max-width: 640px) {
  .proto-hero h1 { font-size: 3rem; }

  .proto-card {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    padding: 2rem;
  }

  .proto-icon svg {
    width: 40px;
    height: 40px;
  }
}
</style>
